    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Despite multiple credibility factor gaps, the assessment team accepted the package under a risk-informed decision framework acknowledging that the mesh independence study (performed as a formal verification activity) provides sufficient discretization error characterization for the intended regulatory submission stage. The team noted that the GCI results are discussed in the validation narrative and that the Monte Carlo UQ bounds provide adequate coverage of inlet boundary condition uncertainty. Remaining gaps in model form, use error, and test sample adequacy are acknowledged as open items for the next assessment cycle.",
